<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - ROCKER ARM
        ASSEMBLY - REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate all rocker arm bushings with clean engine oil, install a retaining ring at one end
                of the shaft and assemble the components with the shaft in the vertical position (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150511">5.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Arrange the rocker arm assembly components as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150512">5.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4150511" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12076" filename="../figcg1/CG12076.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.11 Assemble Rocker Arm Components With Shaft in Vertical Position.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150512" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11329" filename="../figcg1/CG11329.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.12 Rocker Arm Assembly Components.</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The rocker shaft is marked with the word "TOP" in the center of the shaft. This should face up
                        at all times. The brackets must line up over the shaft bolt grooves. An end view position of
                        shaft to bracket is shown in Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_79.xml" xrefid="ef4150513">5.13</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When all components are on the shaft, in the correct order, install the second retaining
                ring to secure the components. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_79.xml" xrefid="ef4150514">5.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Cup plugs (at each end of the shaft) are replaceable. Do not disturb unless damaged or
                        leaking. If replacement is required, pry the damaged plug out and press in a new cup plug. Refer
                        to Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_79.xml" xrefid="ef4150513">5.13</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
